                  <acquisition notAfter="1556">Probably the book with 2<hi rend="superscript">o</hi>f<hi rend="superscript">o</hi>
                     <hi rend="italic">quisque</hi> assigned to Richard Friendship in the <hi rend="italic">electio</hi> of 1519 (UO63. 321). Certainly at the College by 1556 (UO65. 87). At the head of f. 1 is the James no. ‘237’, s. xvii in. Inside the front board is a sheet of paper with a table of contents, s. xvii, ‘N. 4. 15 Art.’, s. xvii, canc. and replaced with ‘B. 3. 5 (LIV)’ in red. ‘15’ is inked on the foredge.</acquisition>
